1502.definition: [εἴκω] apparently a primary verb; properly, to be weak, i.e. yield

1503.definition: [εἴκω] apparently a primary verb (perhaps akin to {{G1502}} through the idea of faintness as a copy); to resemble

1504.definition: [εἰκών] from {{G1503}}; a likeness, i.e. (literally) statue, profile, or (figuratively) representation, resemblance

1506.definition: [εἰλικρινής] from εἵλη (the sun's ray) and {{G2919}}; judged by sunlight, i.e. tested as genuine (figuratively)

1507.definition: [εἱλίσσω] a prolonged form of a primary but defective verb εἵλω (of the same meaning); to coil or wrap See also {{G1667}}.

1509.definition: [εἰ μή τι] from {{G1508}} and the neuter of {{G5100}}; if not somewhat

1510.definition: [εἰμί] the first person singular present indicative; a prolonged form of a primary and defective verb; I exist (used only when emphatic) See also {{G1488}}, {{G1498}}, {{G1511}}, {{G1526}}, {{G2258}}, {{G2071}}, {{G2070}}, {{G2075}}, {{G2076}}, {{G2771}}, {{G2468}}, {{G5600}}.

1511.definition: [εἶναι] present infinitive from {{G1510}}; to exist come, is, X lust after, X please well, there is, to be, was.

1515.definition: [εἰρήνη] probably from a primary verb εἴρω (to join); peace (literally or figuratively); by implication, prosperity

1517.definition: [εἰρηνοποιέω] from {{G1518}}; to be a peace-maker, i.e. (figuratively) to harmonize

1519.definition: [εἰς] a primary preposition; to or into (indicating the point reached or entered), of place, time, or (figuratively) purpose (result, etc.); also in adverbial phrases Often used in composition with the same general import, but only with verbs (etc.) expressing motion (literally or figuratively).

1520.definition: [εἷς]  (including the neuter (etc.) hen);  a primary numeral; one See also {{G1527}}, {{G3367}}, {{G3391}}, {{G3762}}.

1521.definition: [εἰσάγω] from {{G1519}} and {{G71}}; to introduce (literally or figuratively)

1523.definition: [εἰσδέχομαι] from {{G1519}} and {{G1209}}; to take into one's favor

1524.definition: [εἴσειμι] from {{G1519}} and εἶμι (to go); to enter

1525.definition: [εἰσέρχομαι] from {{G1519}} and {{G2064}}; to enter (literally or figuratively)

1526.definition: [εἰσί] 3rd person plural present indicative of {{G1510}}; they are

1527.definition: [εἷς καθ’ εἷς] from {{G1520}} repeated with {{G2596}} inserted; severally

1529.definition: [εἴσοδος] from {{G1519}} and {{G3598}}; an entrance (literally or figuratively)

1530.definition: [εἰσπηδάω] from {{G1519}} and πηδάω (to leap); to rush in

1531.definition: [εἰσπορεύομαι] from {{G1519}} and {{G4198}}; to enter (literally or figuratively)

1533.definition: [εἰσφέρω] from {{G1519}} and {{G5342}}; to carry inward (literally or figuratively)

1534.definition: [εἶτα] of uncertain affinity; a particle of succession (in time or logical enumeration), then, moreover See also {{G1899}}.

1537.definition: [ἐκ]   or ἐξa primary preposition denoting origin (the point whence action or motion proceeds), from, out (of place, time, or cause; literal or figurative; direct or remote) Often used in composition, with the same general import; often of completion.

1538.definition: [ἕκαστος] as if a superlative of ἕκας (afar); each or every

1539.definition: [ἑκάστοτε] as if from {{G1538}} and {{G5119}}; at every time

1542.definition: [ἑκατονταπλασίων] from {{G1540}} and a presumed derivative of {{G4111}}; a hundred times

1543.definition: [ἑκατοντάρχης]   or ἑκατόνταρχοςfrom {{G1540}} and {{G757}}; the captain of one hundred men

1544.definition: [ἐκβάλλω] from {{G1537}} and {{G906}}; to eject (literally or figuratively)

1545.definition: [ἔκβασις] from a compound of {{G1537}} and the base of {{G939}} (meaning to go out); an exit (literally or figuratively)

1546.definition: [ἐκβολή] from {{G1544}}; ejection, i.e. (specially) a throwing overboard of the cargo

1547.definition: [ἐκγαμίζω] from {{G1537}} and a form of {{G1061}} (compare {{G1548}}); to marry off a daughter

1549.definition: [ἔκγονον] neuter of a derivative of a compound of {{G1537}} and {{G1096}}; a descendant, i.e. (specially) grandchild

1550.definition: [ἐκδαπανάω] from {{G1537}} and {{G1159}}; to expend (wholly), i.e. (figuratively) exhaust

1551.definition: [ἐκδέχομαι] from {{G1537}} and {{G1209}}; to accept from some source, i.e. (by implication) to await

1553.definition: [ἐκδημέω] from a compound of {{G1537}} and {{G1218}}; to emigrate, i.e. (figuratively) vacate or quit

1554.definition: [ἐκδίδωμι] from {{G1537}} and {{G1325}}; to give forth, i.e. (specially) to lease

1555.definition: [ἐκδιηγέομαι] from {{G1537}} and a compound of {{G1223}} and {{G2233}}; to narrate through wholly

1558.definition: [ἔκδικος] from {{G1537}} and {{G1349}}; carrying justice out, i.e. a punisher

1559.definition: [ἐκδιώκω] from {{G1537}} and {{G1377}}; to pursue out, i.e. expel or persecute implacably

1560.definition: [ἔκδοτος] from {{G1537}} and a derivative of {{G1325}}; given out or over, i.e. surrendered

1562.definition: [ἐκδύω] from {{G1537}} and the base of {{G1416}}; to cause to sink out of, i.e. (specially as of clothing) to divest

1563.definition: [ἐκεῖ] of uncertain affinity; there; by extension, thither

1565.definition: [ἐκεῖνος] from {{G1563}}; that one (or (neuter) thing); often intensified by the article prefixed See also {{G3778}}.

1567.definition: [ἐκζητέω] from {{G1537}} and {{G2212}}; to search out, i.e. (figuratively)investigate, crave, demand, (by Hebraism) worship

1570.definition: [ἔκθετος] from {{G1537}} and a derivative of {{G5087}}; put out, i.e. exposed to perish

1573.definition: [ἐκκακέω] from {{G1537}} and {{G2556}}; to be (bad or) weak, i.e. (by implication) to fail (in heart)

1574.definition: [ἐκκεντέω] from {{G1537}} and the base of {{G2759}}; to transfix

1576.definition: [ἐκκλείω] from {{G1537}} and {{G2808}}; to shut out (literally or figuratively)

1577.definition: [ἐκκλησία] from a compound of {{G1537}} and a derivative of {{G2564}}; a calling out, i.e. (concretely) a popular meeting, especially a religious congregation (Jewish synagogue, or Christian community of members on earth or saints in heaven or both)

1578.definition: [ἐκκλίνω] from {{G1537}} and {{G2827}}; to deviate, i.e. (absolutely) to shun (literally or figuratively), or (relatively) to decline (from piety)

1579.definition: [ἐκκολυμβάω] from {{G1537}} and {{G2860}}; to escape by swimming

1580.definition: [ἐκκομίζω] from {{G1537}} and {{G2865}}; to bear forth (to burial)

1581.definition: [ἐκκόπτω] from {{G1537}} and {{G2875}}; to exscind; figuratively, to frustrate

1582.definition: [ἐκκρέμαμαι] middle voice from {{G1537}} and {{G2910}}; to hang upon the lips of a speaker, i.e. listen closely

1585.definition: [ἐκλανθάνομαι] middle voice from {{G1537}} and {{G2990}}; to be utterly oblivious of

1586.definition: [ἐκλέγομαι] middle voice from {{G1537}} and {{G3004}} (in its primary sense); to select

1587.definition: [ἐκλείπω] from {{G1537}} and {{G3007}}; to omit, i.e. (by implication) cease (die)

1590.definition: [ἐκλύω] from {{G1537}} and {{G3089}}; to relax (literally or figuratively)

1591.definition: [ἐκμάσσω] from {{G1537}} and the base of {{G3145}}; to knead out, i.e. (by analogy) to wipe dry

1592.definition: [ἐκμυκτηρίζω] from {{G1537}} and {{G3456}}; to sneer outright at

1593.definition: [ἐκνεύω] from {{G1537}} and {{G3506}}; (by analogy) to slip off, i.e. quietly withdraw

1594.definition: [ἐκνήφω] from {{G1537}} and {{G3525}}; (figuratively) to rouse (oneself) out of stupor

1595.definition: [ἑκούσιον] neuter of a derivative from {{G1635}}; voluntariness

1596.definition: [ἑκουσίως] adverb from the same as {{G1595}}; voluntarily

1597.definition: [ἔκπαλαι] from {{G1537}} and {{G3819}}; long ago, for a long while

1600.definition: [ἐκπετάννυμι] from {{G1537}} and a form of {{G4072}}; to fly out, i.e. (by analogy) to extend
